.tile(data-name='PLM Portal' data-id='portal')
    .tile-image(style="background: url('images/app-portal.jpg') no-repeat;background-size:contain;")
    .tile-details
        .tile-title PLM Portal
        .tile-subtitle Provide quick access to latest product data in PLM using a very basic frontend for casual users, working well on tablets
        .tile-access 
            .tile-endpoint /portal
            .tile-button.button.default(href="portal" target="_blank") Open
            .tile-button.button.icon.icon-start.default(href="https://youtu.be/tM8why6ybAU" target="_blank")
    .instructions
        h1 Features
        p In this easy to use application, users can quickly search for any design or access most recent items to continue where they left. 
            br
            |Once a design is selected, the following features are available:
        ul
            li 3D Viewer with exploded view
            li Item Details
            li Item Attachments
            li BOM with cross-highlight
            li Bulk BOM Files Download
        h1 Define Startup Item 
        p You can pass the parameters dmsId and wsId in your URL to skip the search and let the portal open the given item direclty.
            br
            |Searches are still possible by using the toggle button in the main toolbar.
        img(src='images/apps/portal-1.png' style='width:100%;max-width:1280px;margin:10px 0px 30px;')
        h1 Application Configuration Settings
        p The following application specific settings can be adjusted in your custom settings file in 
            span.code exports.applications.portal 
            br
            |In order to change any of these settings, copy the standard value from settings.js to your custom settings file in folder settings.
        table.row-hovering 
            tr 
                th Setting 
                th Default Value
                th Description 
            tr 
                td workspaceId
                td null
                td The ID of the Items workspaces. This value is set to null per default to reuse the ID of settings 
                    span.code common.workspaceIds.items
            tr 
                td viewingFormats
                td null
                td The file formats to use when rendering the selected item in the viewer. This value is set to null per default to reuse the standard value of 
                    span.code common.viewer.extensionsIncluded
            tr 
                td autoClick
                td true
                td When set to true and the search returns one result only, the given item will be selected automatically
            tr 
                td openMostRecent
                td true
                td When set to true the first item of the Recent Items list will be opened automatically
            tr 
                td panels
                td { insertSearch : [], insertRecentItems : []}
                td This setting and its nodes can be used to adjust the various panels of the application based on the standard configuration capabilities of the given panels for Searches, the Recently Viewed list, BOM trees, Item Details pages and the Files panel.
        h1 Common Configuration Settings
        p This utility uses the following common configuration settings
        table(style='margin:10px 0px 30px')
            tr
                th Setting
                th Default Value 
                th Description
            tr  
                td exports.common.workspaceIds.items
                td 57
                td The default ID of the Items workspace
            tr  
                td exports.common.viewer.extensionsIncluded
                td ['dwf', 'dwfx', 'nwd', ...]
                td The sequence of file formats to use when rendering the items in the viewer. The first format being available will be used.
            tr  
                td exports.common.workspaces.items.defaultBOMView
                td 'Tree Navigator'
                td The default BOM view to be used for the BOM display. 
                    br
                    |If the defined view does not exist, the default BOM view will be used instead.
                    br
                    |For best performance, it is recommended to use a BOM view containing only the columns Descriptor, Number and Quantity.
        h1 Viewer Configuration Settings
        include ../framework/viewer.pug
